Interface CalendarView.CalendarAdapter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CalendarView.SimpleCalendarAdapter
    Enclosing class:
    CalendarView

    public static interface CalendarView.CalendarAdapter
    Interface for adapter that provides data set of months for CalendarView.
    Author:
    Martin Albedinsky

    • Method Detail

      • setOnMonthDaySelectionListener

        void setOnMonthDaySelectionListener(@Nullable
                                    CalendarView.OnMonthDaySelectionListener listener)
        Registers a callback to be invoked whenever a specific day is selected within a MonthView at a specific position.
        Parameters:
        listener - Listener callback. May be null to clear the current one.

      • setMinMaxDate

        void setMinMaxDate(long minDateInMillis,
                   long maxDateInMillis)
        Sets a date boundaries for months data set of this adapter. These dates are used to resolve when the months data set should start and how large (in count of months) should be.
        Parameters:
        minDateInMillis - The desired minimum date in milliseconds.
        maxDateInMillis - The desired maximum date in milliseconds.
        See Also:
        getDateMinInMillis(), getDateMaxInMillis()

      • getDateMinInMillis

        long getDateMinInMillis()
        Returns the minimum date specified via setMinMaxDate(long, long) used to resolve start of months data set.
        Returns:
        Minimum date in milliseconds.

      • getDateMaxInMillis

        long getDateMaxInMillis()
        Returns the maximum date specified via setMinMaxDate(long, long) used to limit count of months available.
        Returns:
        Maximum date in milliseconds.

      • setSelectedDate

        void setSelectedDate(@Nullable
                     Long dateInMillis)
        Sets a date that should be selected in months data set of this adapter.
        Parameters:
        dateInMillis - The desired date in milliseconds that will be used to resolve in which month to select the desired day.

      • calculateMonthPosition

        int calculateMonthPosition(int year,
                           int month)
        Calculates a position of a month for the given year and month.
        Parameters:
        year - The desired year number.
        month - The desired month number from the range [Calendar.JANUARY, Calendar.DECEMBER].
        Returns:
        Computed position of the requested month within the current data set.

      • calculateMonthPosition

        int calculateMonthPosition(long dateInMillis)
        Calculates the position of a month with the specified dateInMillis.
        Parameters:
        dateInMillis - The date in milliseconds of month of which position to calculate.
        Returns:
        The calculated month position.

      • getMonthDate

        long getMonthDate(int position)
        Returns the date for a month from this adapter's data set at the specified position.
        Parameters:
        position - Position of the month for which to return its associated date.
        Returns:
        Month's date in milliseconds.
